cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the relationship between human perception and computer vision, specifically deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of DNN models, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the generalization ability of DNNs, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The theoretical view that properties of human perception are a consequence of architecture-independent visual learning falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the applicability of using DNN computation to estimate perceptual loss, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
